net.dempsy.container

Class Container

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.dempsy.container.Container
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, KeyspaceChangeListener, OutputInvoker, Service
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    LockingContainer, NonLockingAltContainer, NonLockingContainer

    public abstract class Container
extends Object
implements Service, KeyspaceChangeListener, OutputInvoker

    The Container manages the lifecycle of message processors for the node that it's instantiated in.

    The container is simple in that it does no thread management. When it's called it assumes that the transport has provided the thread that's needed

      • getMessageWorkingCount

        public abstract int getMessageWorkingCount()
        The number of messages the container is currently working on. This may not match the stats collector's numberOfInFlight messages which is a measurement of how many messages are currently being handled by MPs. This represents how many messages have been given dispatched to the container that are yet being processed. It includes internal queuing in the container as well as messages actually in Mp handlers.

      • invokeOutput

        public void invokeOutput()
        Description copied from interface: OutputInvoker

        This method will be called by client application to invoke the @Output methods of MPs. Dempsy will execute the @Output method of all MPs. During the Output execution, MP will not receive any incoming message.

        Specified by:

      • setOutputConcurrency

        public void setOutputConcurrency(int concurrency)
        Description copied from interface: OutputInvoker
        If the OutputScheduler wants the container to run the Output pass in a multithreaded manner, then calling this method and setting the concurrency to greater than 1 will do that. This method will usually be called once, at initialization. Each time it's called the Executor used by the container will be recreated with all of its attending threads so this method should not be called with each invokeOutput call.
        Specified by:
        setOutputConcurrency in interface OutputInvoker
        Parameters:
        concurrency - is the number of threads to allow Output to be run simultaneously.
